main event: Five individuals observed two orange cones of light moving in a straight path from Kankakee to Chicago on July 11, 1962.
interesting points: The cones of light were estimated to be 3-12 feet long,The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes,The witnesses used binoculars to observe the objects,The objects disappeared over the horizon,The report was submitted by the Base Operations Officer of the 69th Troop Carrier Squadron.
